occurrenceRemarks: Visual Description: This organism is a grey color, with spots on its wings. It has 6 legs. When it expands its wings, there is a red color on the backside of the wings. It is approximately 2 inches long. Habitat: This organism was found on the sidewalk. It was originally sitting on top of a tree, until it flew onto the sidewalk. Geographic Distribution: This organism can be found in China. It is an invasive species that has started appearing in North America, especially in colder regions, such as the State, Pennsylvania. Reference: https://www.invasivespeciesinfo.gov/terrestrial/invertebrates/spotted-lanternfly#:~:text=USDA%20.,Berks%20County%2C%20Pennsylvania%20in%202014.
